(57, 'Contract offer', '-', '-', 'Contract offer', 'Please check the validity of your data in the contract', '<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:1pt solid windowtext; width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; vertical-align:top; width:50%\">\r\n			<p>WHEREAS, VERA FUND, LLC is engaged in the business of purchasing and managing real estate property in USA;</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p>WHEREAS, VERA FUND, LLC is engaged in the renovations, management, leasing of the purchased properties and leasing or selling this property to make a profit for a CLIENT;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>WHEREAS, VERA FUND, LLC and CLIENT (the &ldquo;PARTIES&rdquo;) desire to collaborate in purchasing real estate property in USA(the &ldquo;WORK&rdquo;);</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>WHEREAS, the PARTIES desire that the WORK be governed by the terms and conditions set forth herein;</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p>NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and Agreements contained herein, and the benefits to be derived by both PARTIES, CLIENT and VERA FUND, LLC agree as follows:</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>1. CLIENT&rsquo;S INFORMATION</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>CLIENT agrees to provide accurate, current, and complete information required to register with VERA FUND, LLC, and other information required after registration. VERA FUND, LLC has the right to terminate CLIENT&rsquo;s rights to services if any information provided by CLIENT is false or incomplete. CLIENT agrees that VERA FUND, LLC may store for future reference personal Client information provided through for above services.</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<p><strong>2. SERVICES</strong><br />\r\n			CLIENT is entitled to access property information by using http://vera.fund website. All properties presented via web-based platform at http://vera.fund</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>CLIENT will see details about property requested via pressing more details button on the http://vera.fund website. This will let the CLIENT know all details of the property available within crowdfunding platform.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>3. DEPOSITS AND FEES</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>CLIENT shall transfer to the VERA FUND, LLC&rsquo;s account a minimum amount of <u>$1000 (one thousand)</u> if participating in purchasing of residential property. CLIENT shall transfer to the VERA FUND, LLC&rsquo;s account a minimum amount of <u>$10000 (ten thousand)</u> if participating in purchasing of commercial property.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>CLIENT will pay VERA FUND, LLC a fee in the amount of <u>two-percent (2%)</u> of the investment amount. Also, CLIENT will pay VERA FUND, LLC a <u>ten percent (10%)</u> fee for property management which is calculated based on income from rent or resale less the expenses. All the fees must be paid after the property acquired or leased.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>4. INVESTOR&rsquo;S INVESTMENTS</strong><br />\r\n			Investor agrees to invest in the Property the sum set forth in Annex I hereto (the &ldquo;Investment&rdquo;), in accordance with the terms and conditions set forth herein, including Annex I hereto, and such other terms and conditions that may be agreed to by the Parties from time to time. The exact sum of the investment shall be confirmed upon actual receipt of funds from the Investor.</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<p><strong>5. THE PROPERTY AND ACQUISIYION</strong><br />\r\n			The Property address is ____________________________________. The Company has acquired an exclusive call option to purchase the Property for the amount of USD_____________ (_______________________) (the &ldquo;Call Option&rdquo;). Investors may contribute funds towards the cost of acquisition of the Property, as set forth in the Call Option, plus costs and expenses, including reasonable insurance and applicable taxes (collectively, the &ldquo;Cost of Acquisition&rdquo;).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>If the Cost of Acquisition is raised in full, the Property will be acquired, with ownership thereof reflected as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(i) Title to the Property shall be placed in the name of the Company; and (ii) investors who have contributed towards the</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Acquisition of the Property shall become shareholders of Class B Shares of VERA FUND, LLC (the &ldquo;Offering&rdquo;). The</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Offering shall not be available to any person or entity in any jurisdiction where it would be contrary to applicable laws, rules or regulations of any governmental authority or where Manager, or the Company, is not authorized to make such Offering.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>6. CLIENT ACCOUNT, PRIVACY AND SECURITY</strong><br />\r\n			As registered Investor under VERA FUND, LLC, CLIENT will be registered under an account. CLIENT is responsible for maintaining a fiduciary relationship with VERA FUND, LLC. CLIENT should not reveal account information to anyone else, except VERA FUND, LLC, or use anyone else&rsquo;s account. CLIENT is entirely responsible for all activities that occur on or through the account, and agrees to immediately notify VERA FUND, LLC of any unauthorized use of the account or any other breach of security. VERA FUND, LLC shall not be responsible for any losses arising out of the unauthorized use of the account.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p>VERA FUND, LLC is committed to CLIENTS right to privacy. VERA FUND, LLC will never rent or sell CLIENTS private information to anyone.</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<p><strong>7. VIOLATIONS / INDEMNIFICATION</strong><br />\r\n			CLIENT agrees, at CLIENTS own expense, to defend and indemnify and hold harmless VERA FUND, LLC against all third party claims, losses, liability, damages, and/or costs, including reasonable attorney&rsquo;s fees that may not asserted against VERA FUND, LLC and all losses incurred, as a result of any violations of this Agreement by CLIENT.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>8. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES</strong></p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Information provided by VERA FUND, LLC is believed to be accurate and reliable, but no warranties are made as to the accuracy or timeliness of Content.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>In order to provide CLIENT with this service, VERA FUND, LLC is unable to offer any warranties or make any representations about any benefits or opportunities that CLIENT may obtain. VERA FUND, LLC hereby disclaims all warranties, express or implied, including, but not limited to, warranties of merchantability, fitness for particular purpose, title, and non-infringement. Auction analysis which CLIENT gets by the mail is made available to CLIENT &ldquo;As Is&rdquo;, without any warranties whatsoever about the nature, content, or accuracy (either when posted or as a result of the passage of time) of any material, and without any representations or guaranties. In addition, VERA FUND, LLC makes no representations, warranties or guarantees that the analysis will be secure, accessible continuously and without interruption, or error free. To the extent that client might otherwise believe that any warranties, guarantees or representations have been made to CLIENT, CLIENT hereby agrees that such statement, whether made orally or in writing, are to be construed as merely nonbinding expressions of policy rather than affirmative representations, obligations, guarantees or warranties. In the event of any conflict between this section eight and other terms or provisions of this agreement, this section shall be constructed to take precedence.</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<p><strong>9. DISPUTE RESOLUTION / JURISDICTION</strong><br />\r\n			VERA FUND, LLC is a registered company in Florida. All disputes arising out of the relating to this agreement shall be resolved by binding arbitration in the state of Florida, pursuant to the rules of the American Arbitration Association. All such disputes shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the United States and the State of Florida governing contracts made and to be performed in that State. However, CLIENT agrees that VERA FUND, LLC shall be entitled to obtain preliminary injunctive relief to enforce any of the terms of this agreement against CLIENT pending final determination in arbitration.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>10.SHARE ISSUANCE</strong><br />\r\n			The Manager has been authorized to issue two series of shares: Class A Shares and Class B Shares. Class A Shares have management and voting rights. Class B Shares shall have no management or voting rights, but shall have economic rights. Class B Shares are not convertible to Class A Shares. Manager owns all of the issued Class A Shares</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>of VERA FUND LLC and offers Investor the opportunity to purchase Class B Shares of VERA FUND LLC equivalent to the Investor&acute;s Investment (the &ldquo;Shares B&rdquo;).</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>11. THE CLASS B SHARES SUBSCRIPTION. </strong><br />\r\n			Class B shares shall each have a par value of EUR 1 (One Euro). Within 30 (Thirty)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>days from the date the Property is purchased (the &ldquo;Purchase Date&rdquo;), the Manager shall issue in favor of Investor a number of Class B Shares equivalent to Investor&rsquo;s Investment in the Property. The Class B Shares shall be delivered to Investor</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>within 45 (Forty Five) days from the Purchase Date upon written request. The Class B Shares shall be subscribed by Investor unencumbered, free and clear of all liens. Investor shall have no right to encumber such Class B Shares. The Class</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>B Shares shall be subject to restrictions on transferability and resale, and may not be transferred or resold except as permitted by the By-laws and Shareholders Agreement of VERA FUND LLC.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>INVESTMENT IN SHARES INVOLVES A HIGH DEGREE OF RISK AND IS SUITABLE ONLY FOR THOSE INVESTORS WHOHAVE SUBSTANTIAL FINANCIAL RESOURCES IN RELATION TO THEIR INVESTMENT AND WHO UNDERSTAND THEPARTICULAR RISK FACTORS OF THIS INVESTMENT. IN ADDITION, INVESTMENT IN THE SHARES IS SUITABLE ONLY FORAN INVESTOR WHO DOES NOT NEED LIQUIDITY IN HIS, HER OR ITS INVESTMENT, AND IS WILLING TO ACCEPTRESTRICTIONS ON THE TRANSFER OF THE SHARES. INVESTOR IS ADVISED TO CONSULT WITH HIS INVESTMENT<br />\r\n			ADVISOR PRIOR TO ENTERING INTO THIS AGREEMENT.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>12. INVESTOR REPRESENTATION </strong><br />\r\n			(i) Non-U.S. or UK Person. Investor represents and warrants that Investor is not a U.S. person, as such term is</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>defined in 17 C.F.R. &sect;230.902(k)(1) issued pursuant to the Securities Act of 1933, as amended from time to time, or asubject of the United Kingdom (&ldquo;US or UK Person&rdquo;). In addition, Investor agrees that he shall have no right to transfer anyof the Class B Shares to a US or UK Person or to market the Class B Shares in the USA or the UK. Investor agrees and</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>understands that Manager is entering into this Term Sheet outside of the USA and in reliance on the representations madeby Investor herein.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(ii) Capital or Income Requirements. Should the Investor be a national or resident of a jurisdiction that</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>establishes minimum capital or income requirements for Investor to be eligible to accept the Offering: (a) It is Investor&acute;sresponsibility to ensure Investor complies with said requirements; (b) Investor hereby represents and warrants to</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Company that Investor complies with such requirements; and, (c) Company may justifiably rely upon said Investorrepresentation of compliance to proceed with the investment transaction.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(iii) Knowledge and Experience to Invest. Investor further represents and warrants that: (a) He has sufficient</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>knowledge and experience in finances and business to evaluate the risks and the content of the Offering and that he iscapable of assuming said risks; (b) He has had access to information regarding the Offering which he deems necessary andsufficient to make the investment decision; and, (c) Is aware that the Offering shall be null and void in the event it issubject to registration requirements in the jurisdiction of his nationality or permanent residence.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>13. LEASE</strong><br />\r\n			As soon as practicable after the Purchase Date, the Manager shall offer the Property for lease (the&ldquo;Lease&rdquo;). The Lease monthly rent has been appraised to be approximately USD ______ (___________________________),</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>from which amount Manager shall pay reasonable expenses, including insurance and applicable taxes.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>14. SALE OF PROPERTY</strong><br />\r\n			Always after four years or, if, at any time within the first two years, the Property&acute;s increase in valueexceeds 20% (Twenty Percent) of the Purchase Price, as confirmed by two independent professionals, the followingprocedure for sale of the Property (the &ldquo;Sale&rdquo;) shall apply:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(i) The Manager shall have the Property appraised and placed on the market at market value;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(ii) In case the placing on sale of the Property was activated due to an increase in value of 20% (Twenty Percent) withinthe first two years, the sale will not proceed if the increase in value drops below 20% (Twenty Percent).Twice a year Manager shall request an appraisal of the Property to determine the Property&acute;s value.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>15. DISTRIBUTIONS</strong><br />\r\n			Investor shall have the right to collect profits on a pro rata basis based on the number of Class B Sharesowned, as follows: The Company&acute;s income shall be distributed to its sole member, after payment of all applicable taxes,expenses and management fees. The Manager shall, in turn, distribute profits in the form of dividends to Investor, prorata, once per year, after payment of all applicable taxes and expenses.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>16. INVESTOR&rsquo;S REDEMPTION RIGHTS</strong><br />\r\n			Manager expressly represents and Investor expressly acknowledges that Class B</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Shares do not have the right of redemption. Investor may transfer his Class B Shares to any third party, provided always</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>that such transfer is undertaken in full compliance with the transfer process described in the By-laws and Shareholders</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Agreement and with Manager&acute;s prior written approval, which shall not be unreasonably denied. Investor shall be solelyresponsible for the payment of any costs incurred throughout such process, including but not limited to, legalconsultations and administrative costs. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Investor shall have no rights to transfer the Class B</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Shares to a U.S. Person or to market the Shares B in the United States or to U.S. Persons.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>17. TERM</strong><br />\r\n			Manager shall have 45 (Forty Five) days from the date of Closing (the &ldquo;First Period&rdquo;) to purchase the Property</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or another similar property (a &ldquo;Similar Property&rdquo;, as described below). During the First Period, Investor may not reclaim</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or withdraw the Investment. In the event the First Period is finalized without the Company having purchased the Property</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>or any other Similar Property, Investor may request Manager to refund the Investment and, if Investor so requests, the</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Investment shall be transferred to Investor as soon as practicable, without any interest and /or penalty to be claimed from</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Manager.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>18. SIMILAR PROPERTIES</strong><br />\r\n			Investor hereby authorizes Manager to purchase the Property. In the event that, for any reason</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>not attributable to Manager, the Property cannot be purchased, Investor authorizes Manager to negotiate the purchase of any other real estate property similar to the Property, in Manager&rsquo;s sole discretion, located in the same city in which the Property is located and situated no more than 20 Km (Twenty Kilometers) from the Property, with a similar total area as</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>the Property and promise to generate a similar rental income (&ldquo;Similar Property&rdquo;).</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>19. CLOSING/INVESTMENT TRANSFER</strong><br />\r\n			The closing of the Offering shall take place at the Closing, the date on which the Costof Acquisition is fully financed. Upon execution of this Term Sheet, Investor shall transfer 100% (One Hundred Percent) ofthe Investment to the bank account indicated by Manager, ensuring that it be received within 6 (Six) business daystherefrom (the &ldquo;Investment Payment Term&rdquo;).</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p>The Investor&rsquo;s Investment shall be kept in trust in the account indicated byManager, until such time as the Property is acquired on the Purchase Date.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Should the Investment not be received withinthe Investment Payment Term, this Term Sheet will become null and void, which shall be advised in writing by Manager toInvestor.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Manager shall inform Investor in writing in the event the Closing is cancelled or postponed.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Otherwise, it shall beunderstood that Closing shall take place as set forth above.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p>Following the Closing, the following shall take place on the Purchase Date:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(i) Company shall purchase the Property or any other Similar Property.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(ii) The Manager shall issue in favor of Investor the Class B Shares corresponding pro rata to Investor Investment.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(iii) Definitive Agreements (as defined below) shall be executed.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>20. INVESTOR BREACH</strong><br />\r\n			If 100% (One Hundred Percent) of Investor Investment is not received in the bank account to be indicated by Manager within 6 (Six) business days from the date of execution of this Term Sheet, Investor shall forfeit hisright to participate in the Offering or the Project.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>21. MANAGER</strong><br />\r\n			Manager shall act as manager of VERA FUND LLC Limited and of the Company, and shall manage the day to day operations of the Company and the Property. Investor shall have no right to participate in the day to day operations ofVERA FUND LLC, the Company or the Property.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>22. POWER OF ATTORNEY</strong><br />\r\n			On the Purchase Date, Investor shall hereby, without the requirement of any further instrument,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>irrevocably constitute and appoint the Manager its attorney and agent to sign, execute and deliver, in his name and on hisbehalf, all or any such agreement, deeds, instruments, documents and/or any counterpart thereof or certificates or to takeany such action as it deems necessary from time to time or as is required under any applicable law to admit Investor as ashareholder of VERA FUND, LLC, including (without limitation) the power and authority to sign, execute and deliver</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(or attach signature pages to) all agreements (including underwriting agreements), securities, instruments or documents,or any counterpart thereof, in relation to:</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(i) any transfers of shares in VERA FUND, LLC; or</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(ii) the admission of any shareholder to VERA FUND, LLC.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>This power of attorney shall be granted to secure the obligations of Investor hereunder and shall be irrevocable.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>23. DEFINITIVE AGREEMENTS</strong><br />\r\n			On the Purchase Date the Parties shall execute definitive agreements, which may include,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>among others, the subscription agreement to VERA FUND, LLC, the Power of Attorney in favor of Manager, the</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Shareholders Agreement of VERA FUND, LLC and any other agreement required to implement the terms and</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>conditions hereof (collectively, hereinafter the &ldquo;Definitive Agreements&rdquo;). The Definitive Agreements shall contain termsconsistent with the terms of this Term Sheet and other customary terms for transactions of this nature. The DefinitiveAgreements will also contain representations, warranties, covenants and indemnities for transactions similar to the onedescribed herein.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>24. CONFIDENTIALITY</strong><br />\r\n			The Parties hereto covenant and agree (and agree to make reasonable efforts to cause their</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>employees, agents, affiliates or potential investors) not to disclose any information of a confidential or proprietary natureprovided by the other Party (collectively, the &ldquo;Confidential Information&rdquo;), except (i) information previously indicated by</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>disclosing Party as permitted for distribution to any third party, (ii) pursuant to a subpoena or order issued by a court,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>arbitrator or governmental body, agency or official binding upon not disclosing Party, (iii) pursuant to any othergovernmental requirements (e.g., securities law requirements) binding upon the non-disclosing Party, (iv) to the extentany such Confidential Information comes into the public domain other than as a result of disclosure by the non-disclosing</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Party, or (v) with the prior written consent of disclosing Party. If non disclosing Party shall receive a request to discloseany Confidential Information under a subpoena or order, non-disclosing Party shall (a) promptly notify disclosing Party,</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(b) consult with disclosing Party on the advisability of taking steps to resist or narrow such request and (c) if disclosure isrequired or deemed advisable, reasonably co-operate with disclosing Party in any attempt it may make to obtain an orderor other assurance that confidential treatment will be accorded such Confidential Information, as the case may be, that isdisclosed.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>25. EXPENCES</strong><br />\r\n			Each Party shall pay its own costs and expenses incurred in connection with the execution of this Term</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Sheet and the Investor&rsquo;s Investment (including fees and expenses of financial advisors, financial sponsors, legal counsel</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>and other advisors, travel, etc.).</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>26. TAXES</strong><br />\r\n			Each party shall be responsible for the payment of their own taxes resulting from the Investment.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>27. INDEMNITY</strong><br />\r\n			The Company, VERA FUND, LLC and Investor shall indemnify Manager to the full extent permittedby law for any claims against Manager in connection with the matters contained herein, except in the event of Manager&rsquo;sgross negligence or willful misconduct.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>28. COOPERATION</strong><br />\r\n			The Parties hereto agree to cooperate fully and in good faith to complete the transaction describedherein as expeditiously as possible.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>29. TERMINATION</strong><br />\r\n			Except as otherwise provided herein, Investor may not terminate this Term Sheet. Manager may</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>terminate this Term Sheet, at its sole discretion, prior to the Purchase Date, in which case, the Investment shall be</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>refunded to Investor without any interest and/or penalty, except as otherwise indicated in this Term Sheet</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>30. ATTORNEY&rsquo;S FEES</strong><br />\r\n			In the event of a dispute with regard to the provisions of this Term Sheet, the prevailing Party shallbe entitled to collect reasonable attorneys&rsquo; fees and costs from the other Party.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>31. ASSIGNMENT</strong><br />\r\n			Investor may not assign his rights and obligations under this Term Sheet, without the prior writtenconsent of the Manager. Manager may transfer its rights and obligations to any related party.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>32. NOTICES/DOMICILES.</strong><br />\r\n			Unless otherwise provided herein, any notice required or permitted under this Term Sheet shallbe given in writing and shall be deemed effectively given upon personal delivery to the Party to be notified or upon deposit</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with an internationally-recognized express courier, or by registered or certified mail, postage prepaid and addressed tothe Party to be notified at the address indicated for such Party below, or at such other address as such Party may designate</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>with 10 (Ten) days&rsquo; written notice to the other Parties.</p>\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n			<p><strong>33. SUCCESSORTS AND ASSIGNS.</strong><br />\r\n			This Term Sheet shall be binding upon and shall inure to the benefit of the Parties heretoand their respective heirs, executors, administrators, successors and permitted assigns.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><strong>34. ENTIRE AGREEMENT.</strong><br />\r\n			This Term Sheet, including any other documents referred to herein which form an integral partthereof, except for those matters to be defined in the Definitive Agreements, contains the entire understanding of theParties hereto with respect to the subject matter contained herein and therein, and no Party shall be liable or bound to anyother Party in any manner by any warranties, representations, or covenants, except as specifically set forth herein or</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>therein. This Term Sheet supersedes all prior or simultaneous written and oral agreements and understandings among the</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>parties with respect to such subject matter.</p>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<p><br />\r\n			<strong>35. WAIVERS AND 